{
  "id": "helix-agent-roles",
  "title": "Add agent-roles.md context file defining specialized agent roles for the WC library",
  "category": "automation",
  "description": "Create `.automaker/context/agent-roles.md` to define specialized agent roles optimized for the Helix web component library's quality bar and conventions.\n\n## Roles to define\n\n- **Component Architect**: Creates new Lit 3.x components following all conventions, adds Vitest tests, Storybook stories, and CEM\n- **Token Engineer**: Manages design token additions/changes, updates CSS exports and Lit bindings\n- **Documentation Writer**: Updates Starlight docs, JSDoc, and Storybook autodocs\n- **Quality Auditor**: Runs all 7 quality gates, identifies and fixes failures\n- **A11y Specialist**: Audits components for WCAG 2.1 AA compliance, fixes violations\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Create `.automaker/context/agent-roles.md` with descriptions of each role\n2. For each role: include responsibilities, which files to touch, which commands to run, what the acceptance criteria are\n3. Reference the coding-rules.md and CLAUDE.md for constraints\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- File exists at `.automaker/context/agent-roles.md`\n- All 5 roles are defined with clear scope and responsibilities\n- Each role references specific commands from the project",
